From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: das <das@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 27 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Fix unbound NIX_STORE variable in functional test
 infrastructure

On non-NixOS systems, NIX_STORE is not set. With bash's `set -u`
(nounset) mode, the bare `$NIX_STORE` reference on line 47 of
tests/functional/common/vars.sh causes an "unbound variable" error,
making ALL functional tests fail immediately.

Fix: use `${NIX_STORE-}` to default to empty string when unset.

This affects any non-NixOS test environment (e.g., Ubuntu on s390x).
---
 tests/functional/common/vars.sh | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tests/functional/common/vars.sh b/tests/functional/common/vars.sh
index a6b83ae4e..07247cf24 100644
--- a/tests/functional/common/vars.sh
+++ b/tests/functional/common/vars.sh
@@ -44,7 +44,7 @@ if ! isTestOnNixOS; then
   export NIX_DAEMON_SOCKET_PATH=$TEST_ROOT/dSocket
   unset NIX_USER_CONF_FILES
   export _NIX_TEST_SHARED=$TEST_ROOT/shared
-  if [[ -n $NIX_STORE ]]; then
+  if [[ -n ${NIX_STORE-} ]]; then
       export _NIX_TEST_NO_SANDBOX=1
   fi
   export _NIX_IN_TEST=$TEST_ROOT/shared
--
